&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;Sorter Operator &lt;/strong&gt;is an individual who aids plant staff in preparing material for processing, baling, inventorying, and shipment. They are familiar or can become familiar with a fast-paced manufacturing environment and working safely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As &lt;/strong&gt;our&lt;strong&gt; Sorter Operator,&lt;/strong&gt; you will work to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Segregate various materials including cardboard, paper, plastic, and aluminum in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep the plant and areas clean of debris.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean equipment as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a reliable attendance record.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members to provide comprehensive training for new employees, ensuring they are well-equipped with the necessary skills and knowledge to perform their roles effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned by the supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be flexible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent teamwork skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to stand for eight or more hours with the occasional need to bend or squat&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate in a high speed and fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift 45 pounds repeatedly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to follow instructions as directed by the supervisor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in hot and cold environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
